text: Storm Warning! is the fourth Dick Morrissey Quartet album. It was recorded live at The Bull's Head, London, in November 1965.Ruppli, M. and Novitsky, E. The Mercury Labels: A Discography. Greenwood Press, 1993 == Track listing == # "Storm Warning" - (Harry South) # "What Is There to Say" - (Vernon Duke, Yip Harburg) # "Come Rain Or Come Shine" - (Harold Arlen, Johnny Mercer) # "Wind of Change" - (Harry South) # "Get Out of Town" - (Cole Porter) # "March On" - (Dick Morrissey) == Personnel == *Dick Morrissey - tenor sax *Harry South - piano *Phil Bates - double bass *Phil Seamen - drums == References == Category:Dick Morrissey albums Category:1965 live albums Category:Mercury Records live albums
title: Storm Warning!
